<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-07T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/25662: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-07T17:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 8—10:44
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>58. Mexican Chargé d’Affaires at Paris arrived today on ceremonial visit
                            to thank Polish Government for participation in recent ceremonies at
                            Mexico City. Foreign Office confident that it is expected he will make
                            strong appeal for recognition present Government of Mexico. I indicated
                            desirability that Government maintain position outlined in my 146, May
                            25 [<hi rend="italic">June 23?</hi>], 1921.<note n="31b" xml:id="d583fn31b"><ref target="frus1921v02#pg_434"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 434</ref>.</note> Request any
                            additional instructions Department may desire to give me.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>